          "scid": "thig3.4:1.0.3",
          "en": "4. Dantika and the Elephant"
        },
        {
          "scid": "thig3.4:1.0.4",
          "en": "Coming out from my day's abiding on Vulture Peak Mountain, I saw on the bank of a river an elephant emerged from its plunge."
        },
        {
          "scid": "thig3.4:1.0.5",
          "en": "A man holding a hook requested: \"Give me your foot.\" The elephant extended its foot. The man got up on the elephant."
        },
        {
          "scid": "thig3.4:1.0.6",
          "en": "Seeing what was untrained now tamed brought under human control, with that I centered my mind — why I'd gone to the woods in the first place."
        }
      ],
